Judeophobia is the fear of Jews, also called as Jewophobia. First used as a counterpoint in the discussion of Islamophobia and anti-Semitism.
Although a phobia is often defined as a strong fear '''or''' dislike, it is not so. Phobia is an irrational or very powerful fear and resulting dislike of something such as spiders or confined spaces. In actuality, the genesis of the dislike is the fear that is first felt.